<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>
        <%= title %>
    </title>
    <%- include('shared/head') %>
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/main.css">
        <style>
            body {
                font-family: "Poppins", "Fredoka One", "Comic Sans MS", sans-serif;
                background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0078d7, #004a8c);
                color: var(--text-color);
                min-height: 100vh;
            }

            .container {
                max-width: 1000px;
                margin: 0 auto;
                padding: 20px;
                padding-top: 80px;
                width: 100%;
                box-sizing: border-box;
            }

            .faq-content {
                background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95);
                border-radius: 16px;
                padding: 40px;
                box-shadow: 0 8px 25px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.25);
                margin-top: 20px;
                position: relative;
                overflow: hidden;
            }

            .faq-content::before {
                content: "";
                position: absolute;
                top: 0;
                left: 0;
                right: 0;
                height: 6px;
                background: linear-gradient(90deg, #ff4500, #ffcc00, #4caf50, #2196f3);
            }

            h1 {
                color: var(--primary-color);
                text-align: center;
                margin-bottom: 30px;
                font-size: 2.8rem;
                text-shadow: 1px 1px 3px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
                position: relative;
            }

            h1::after {
                content: "";
                display: block;
                width: 100px;
                height: 4px;
                background-color: var(--secondary-color);
                margin: 15px auto 0;
                border-radius: 2px;
            }

            h2 {
                color: var(--accent-color);
                margin-top: 40px;
                margin-bottom: 20px;
                font-size: 2rem;
                border-bottom: 3px solid var(--secondary-color);
                padding-bottom: 10px;
                display: inline-block;
            }

            .faq-item {
                margin-bottom: 25px;
                border-bottom: 1px solid #e0e0e0;
                padding-bottom: 20px;
            }

            .faq-item:last-child {
                border-bottom: none;
            }

            .question {
                font-size: 1.3rem;
                font-weight: 600;
                color: var(--primary-color);
                margin-bottom: 15px;
                display: flex;
                align-items: flex-start;
            }

            .question::before {
                content: "Q:";
                font-size: 1.4rem;
                color: var(--accent-color);
                font-weight: 700;
                margin-right: 10px;
                min-width: 30px;
            }

            .answer {
                font-size: 1.15rem;
                line-height: 1.7;
                color: #333;
                margin-left: 30px;
                position: relative;
            }

            .answer::before {
                content: "A:";
                position: absolute;
                left: -30px;
                color: var(--primary-color);
                font-weight: 700;
            }

            .category-title {
                color: var(--accent-color);
                font-size: 1.6rem;
                border-left: 6px solid var(--primary-color);
                padding-left: 15px;
                margin: 40px 0 25px;
                background-color: #f8f8f8;
                padding: 10px 15px;
                border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
            }

            .back-to-home {
                display: block;
                margin: 40px auto 20px;
                text-align: center;
                background-color: var(--primary-color);
                color: white;
                font-size: 1.2rem;
                padding: 12px 30px;
                border-radius: 30px;
                text-decoration: none;
                transition: all 0.3s ease;
                box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
                max-width: 200px;
            }

            .back-to-home:hover {
                background-color: #ff5722;
                transform: translateY(-3px);
                box-shadow: 0 6px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.25);
            }

            @media (max-width: 768px) {
                .container {
                    padding: 15px;
                    padding-top: 80px;
                }

                .faq-content {
                    padding: 25px;
                }

                h1 {
                    font-size: 2.2rem;
                }

                h2 {
                    font-size: 1.6rem;
                }

                .question {
                    font-size: 1.2rem;
                }

                .answer {
                    font-size: 1rem;
                }
            }
        </style>
</head>

<body>
    <%- include('shared/header') %>

        <div class="container">
            <div class="faq-content">
                <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

                <p>Find answers to common questions about UNO Online. If your question isn't covered here, feel free to
                    <a href="/contact">contact us</a>.</p>

                <div class="category-title">Game Basics</div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="question">What is UNO Online?</div>
                    <div class="answer">UNO Online is a digital version of the classic card game UNO. It allows you to
                        play the beloved card game with friends or other players from anywhere with an internet
                        connection.</div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="question">Do I need to create an account to play?</div>
                    <div class="answer">Yes, you need to register for an account to access game features, join games,
                        and track your progress. Registration is free and only requires a username, email, and password.
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="question">How many players can join a single game?</div>
                    <div class="answer">A standard UNO game can accommodate 2-4 players. When creating a game, you can
                        specify the maximum number of players allowed to join.</div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="question">Are the rules the same as the physical card game?</div>
                    <div class="answer">Yes, we follow the official UNO rules. For details on gameplay, check out our <a
                            href="/howtoplay">How to Play</a> page.</div>
                </div>

                <div class="category-title">Account Management</div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="question">How do I change my password?</div>
                    <div class="answer">You can change your password by going to your profile settings. Click on your
                        username in the top right corner, select "Settings," and then choose "Change Password."</div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="question">Can I change my username?</div>
                    <div class="answer">Currently, usernames cannot be changed after registration. Please choose your
                        username carefully when signing up.</div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="question">How do I delete my account?</div>
                    <div class="answer">To delete your account, go to your profile settings, scroll to the bottom, and
                        click on "Delete Account." Please note that this action is permanent and cannot be undone.</div>
                </div>

                <div class="category-title">Gameplay</div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="question">How do I create a new game?</div>
                    <div class="answer">To create a new game, go to the Lobby page and click on "Create New Game." You
                        can then set game options like name, player limit, and visibility (public or private).</div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="question">Can I play with specific friends?</div>
                    <div class="answer">Yes! You can create a private game with a password and share the game details
                        with your friends. They'll need to enter the password to join your game.</div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="question">What happens if I disconnect during a game?</div>
                    <div class="answer">If you disconnect, the system will try to keep your spot for a few minutes. You
                        can rejoin by going back to the same game. After a timeout period, you may be removed from the
                        game.</div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="question">How do I call "UNO"?</div>
                    <div class="answer">When you have only one card left, click the "Call UNO!" button that appears on
                        your screen. If you don't call UNO and another player catches you, you'll have to draw two
                        cards.</div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="question">How do I use Wild cards?</div>
                    <div class="answer">When you play a Wild card, you'll be prompted to choose a color. The next player
                        must play a card of that color or another Wild card.</div>
                </div>

                <div class="category-title">Technical Questions</div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="question">Which browsers are supported?</div>
                    <div class="answer">UNO Online works best on Chrome, Firefox, Safari, and Edge. We recommend keeping
                        your browser updated to the latest version for the best experience.</div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="question">Can I play on mobile devices?</div>
                    <div class="answer">Yes, our website is responsive and works on mobile devices. For the best
                        experience, we recommend using a tablet or device with a larger screen.</div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="question">What should I do if I encounter a bug?</div>
                    <div class="answer">If you encounter any issues, please report them through our <a
                            href="/contact">Contact page</a>. Include details about the problem, steps to reproduce it,
                        and your browser information.</div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="question">Is my data secure?</div>
                    <div class="answer">Yes, we take data security seriously. We use encryption for sensitive
                        information and never share your personal data with third parties. For more details, please
                        review our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.</div>
                </div>

                <a href="/" class="btn back-to-home">Back to Home</a>
            </div>
        </div>

        <script>
            document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
                console.log('FAQ page loaded');
            });
        </script>
</body>

</html>